The King-size pillow which I purchased is heavy. It feels like something from the early 1900s. It appears to be well constructed and is filled with millet hulls on one side and buckwheat hulls on the other.

I was getting tired of waking up with a sore neck every morning. My 3 year old ‘MyPillow’ just wasn’t cutting it anymore. Also as a CPAP user, it is hard to get good support and not fight the hose all night long.

I find that I sleep in one spot most all night long. I have been using this pillow for 2 months now. The pillow provides perfect support for my neck and keeps me perfectly aligned.

I use the millet side up against my head because it conforms better, cradles my head, and keeps my ear from getting sore if i turn my head during the night. Having the buckwheat on the bottom provides the stability and firmness to keep my head from sinking too low.

### THE_VERDICT

This pillow definitely earns a spot in the OTD household. The only thing that has kept me from purchasing a pillow like this in the past is the price. I’ve have gotten to the point where comfort and a great night’s sleep is more important than worry about something as trivial as price when it comes to my health and comfort. I wish I had purchased this pillow or something just like it years ago. I don’t think anyone would be disappointed in this pillow. For those of you on a CPAP, I highly recommend this pillow.
